  "prompt": "What was the public's reaction to Crystal Pepsi?",
  "response": "Crystal Pepsi, launched by PepsiCo in the early 1990s, was met with mixed reactions from the public. Initially, there was a lot of curiosity and excitement about the clear soda that promised the same classic Pepsi taste without the dark color. The novelty generated significant buzz and interest, particularly because it was amidst an era of various experimental food and beverage products.\n\nHowever, that enthusiasm quickly waned. Many consumers reported that the taste was not exactly what they expected, with some describing it as less flavorful or different from regular Pepsi. This discrepancy in taste led to disappointment among some loyal Pepsi fans.\n\nMarketing experts have often cited Crystal Pepsi as a classic example of a product that generated strong initial interest but ultimately failed due to inconsistency with consumer expectations and lack of significant taste appeal. After being discontinued in the mid-90s, Crystal Pepsi has seen a few limited-time revivals over the years, often capitalizing on nostalgia rather than genuine demand. \n\nOverall, while it remains a memorable part of 90s pop culture, Crystal Pepsi is generally regarded as a marketing misstep rather than a successful product innovation.",
